. We show\nthat cLCSs depict trajectories initiated at the location of Chevron spill (Nov.\n2011) as compared to synthetic and satellite trajectories, and the outline of\nthe oil from that accident. There is an agreement between the large-scale oil\nslicks reaching the Brazilian beaches (Aug. 2019 to Feb. 2020) and the cp at\nthe coast. The identification and quantitative description of cLCSs improves\nthe effectiveness of future emergency response to oil spills, contingency\nplanning, rescue operations, larval and fish connectivity assessment, drifter\nlaunch strategies, waste pollutant dispersion and destination.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 17 Aug 2020 21:06:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-19"}
