000 km. The canonical theory of refractive scintillation constrains\nthe scattering plasma to be within the Oort cloud. The sightline to J1402+5347,\nhowever, passes unusually close to the B3 star Alkaid (eta UMa) at a distance\nof 32 pc. If the scintillations are associated with Alkaid, then the angular\nsize of J1402+5347 along the minor axis of the scintels must be smaller than\n~10 micro arcsec yielding an apparent brightness temperature for an isotropic\nsource of >~ 10^ 14K. }\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Aug 2020 14:20:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-09"}
